# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post to named
"boards" (group spaces, identified by `#board-name`) and can also send direct messages to other
users (identified by `@username`). This task adds a new bundled workspace plugin `extensions/pulseboard/`
that follows the identical extension structure as IRC and Nostr — same file layout, same SDK imports,
same patterns for account resolution, message send/receive, setup wizard, and tests.

**No existing files are modified.** Only new files are created under `extensions/pulseboard/`.

---

## PulseBoard Platform Design

| Concept        | Detail                                                                 |
|----------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Auth           | Bearer API token (env `PULSEBOARD_TOKEN`, or `config.token`)          |
| Identity       | `username` field (the bot/user's handle on the platform)              |
| Server URL     | Configurable `serverUrl`, default `https://api.pulseboard.example`    |
| Board targets  | `#board-name` — group chat, analogous to IRC channels                 |
| User targets   | `@username` — direct message                                           |
| Receive        | Long-poll `GET /api/v1/updates?since=<ms>`, returns JSON event array  |
| Send (board)   | `POST /api/v1/boards/{boardId}/messages`                              |
| Send (DM)      | `POST /api/v1/users/{userId}/messages`                                |
| Probe          | `GET /api/v1/me` — returns 200 + `{username, connected}` if valid     |
| Text limit     | **4 000 characters** per message chunk                                 |
| Chat types     | `"direct"` + `"group"`                                                 |

---

## Files to Create (22 total)

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # npm metadata + openclaw config block
├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry
├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry
├── api.ts                        # public barrel (re-exports runtime-api + types)
├── runtime-api.ts                # PluginRuntime re-export (mirrors Nostr pattern)
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                  # ResolvedPulseBoardAccount + account helpers
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema: PulseBoardConfigSchema
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts        # UI hint map for config fields
    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore (getPulseBoardRuntime/set)
    ├── normalize.ts              # normalizeTarget, looksLikeId, isBoard/isUser
    ├── send.ts                   # sendMessagePulseBoard()
    ├── probe.ts                  # probePulseBoard() → ProbeResult
    ├── monitor.ts                # monitorPulseBoardProvider() long-poll loop
    ├── session-route.ts          # resolvePulseBoardOutboundSessionRoute()
    ├── setup-core.ts             # pulseBoardSetupAdapter: ChannelSetupAdapter
    ├── setup-surface.ts          # pulseBoardSetupWizard: ChannelSetupWizard
    ├── channel.ts                # createChatChannelPlugin — main plugin export
    ├── normalize.test.ts         # unit tests: normalizeTarget, looksLikeId
    ├── types.test.ts             # unit tests: resolveAccount, listAccountIds
    ├── send.test.ts              # unit tests: sendMessagePulseBoard (mocked fetch)
    └── channel.test.ts           # unit tests: plugin shape, capabilities
```

